# Vie Locale Analytics

## Closed event name allowlist
Emit **only** the following `event` string values. **Do not invent new names** in code without updating this rule and the analytics schema/dashboards.

```text
app_opened
screen_viewed
tab_changed
commune_switched
cta_clicked
search_submitted
filter_applied
listing_impression
listing_opened
listing_created
listing_updated
listing_archived
listing_deleted
message_thread_opened
message_sent
form_started
form_submitted
form_abandoned
auth_login_success
auth_logout
error_shown
```

## Property rules — no PII
**Forbidden in event props** (any layer: client SDK, server, middleware):
- Email, phone, postal address, free-text message bodies, document contents
- Full person name, government IDs, precise device fingerprint beyond coarse `user_agent` class if used

**Allowed examples:** boolean flags, counts, coarse enums, **opaque UUIDs already used in URLs** (`listing_id`, `commune_id` as UUID), sanitized error codes (`VALIDATION_FAILED`).

## Hygiene
- Keep payloads minimal; aggregate high-cardinality dimensions server-side where possible.
- If product adds consent/opt-out gates, honor them before emitting.
